.TH "drm_bridge_chain_mode_fixup" 9 "drm_bridge_chain_mode_fixup" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_bridge_chain_mode_fixup \- fixup proposed mode for all bridges in the encoder chain
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" drm_bridge_chain_mode_fixup
.BI "(struct drm_bridge *bridge "  ","
.BI "const struct drm_display_mode *mode "  ","
.BI "struct drm_display_mode *adjusted_mode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bridge" 12
bridge control structure
.IP "mode" 12
desired mode to be set for the bridge
.IP "adjusted_mode" 12
updated mode that works for this bridge
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Calls \fIdrm_bridge_funcs.mode_fixup\fP for all the bridges in the
encoder chain, starting from the first bridge to the last.
.SH "NOTE"
the bridge passed should be the one closest to the encoder
.SH "RETURN"
true on success, false on failure
